I might have just built the most overkill RecyclerView extension ever. I'm looking at the code as tears come streaming down my face wondering at the same time why the fuck didn't I simply use a CoordinatorLayout.
You know, it all started pretty innocently with "hey we need a list with sections" and I was like "I ain't using no goddamned library"
Then they were like "oh we're gonna need endless scrolling"
Then they were like "oh we're gonna need expandable sections"
Then they were like "oh we're gonna need different layouts for different items in the list"
At this point things started to go south
So this is a cautionary tale. If someone already built it, just use the fucking library.
You can compile it into a library and stick it on maven central
Result: There are now 14 competing standards
<@U21R4GP5J> why did you end up extending RecyclerView? I think most of those features can be handled at the Adapter level. (different layouts, expandable sections, endless scrolling, etc.)
Oh I didn't actually extend the recyclerview, my bad
